            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== PROJECTS ===== -->
    <section id="projects" class="py-20">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <div class="mb-16 reveal">
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">Projects</h2>
        </div>

        <!-- Project 1 -->
        <div class="project-section reveal">
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-center">
            <div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
                <span class="text-text-dim text-xs tracking-widest" style="font-family: var(--font-mono);">01</span>
                <span class="h-px flex-1 bg-border"></span>
                <span class="text-text-dim text-xs" style="font-family: var(--font-mono);">2026</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-1" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">Stock Portfolio Analyser</h3>
              <p class="text-accent text-sm font-medium mb-5">Real-Time Market Data & Visualisation</p>
              <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">
                I wanted to track my own stock picks without paying for Bloomberg. So I built a tool that pulls live market data, crunches the numbers (Sharpe ratio, moving averages, daily returns), and spits out clean charts — all in under 10 seconds.
              </p>
              <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Generates 5 different visualisations: price comparison, cumulative returns, volatility, moving averages, and portfolio allocation. Pick any stocks, any time period — it handles the rest.
              </p>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
                <span class="skill-tag">Python</span>
                <span class="skill-tag">pandas</span>
                <span class="skill-tag">matplotlib</span>
                <span class="skill-tag">Streamlit</span>
                <span class="skill-tag">yfinance</span>
              </div>
              <a href="https://github.com/IshaanKataria/stock-portfolio-analyser" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-secondary">
                <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 0c-6.626 0-12 5.373-12 12 0 5.302 3.438 9.8 8.207 11.387.599.111.793-.261.793-.577v-2.234c-3.338.726-4.033-1.416-4.033-1.416-.546-1.387-1.333-1.756-1.333-1.756-1.089-.745.083-.729.083-.729 1.205.084 1.839 1.237 1.839 1.237 1.07 1.834 2.807 1.304 3.492.997.107-.775.418-1.305.762-1.604-2.665-.305-5.467-1.334-5.467-5.931 0-1.311.469-2.381 1.236-3.221-.124-.303-.535-1.524.117-3.176 0 0 1.008-.322 3.301 1.23.957-.266 1.983-.399 3.003-.404 1.02.005 2.047.138 3.006.404 2.291-1.552 3.297-1.23 3.297-1.23.653 1.653.242 2.874.118 3.176.77.84 1.235 1.911 1.235 3.221 0 4.609-2.807 5.624-5.479 5.921.43.372.823 1.102.823 2.222v3.293c0 .319.192.694.801.576 4.765-1.589 8.199-6.086 8.199-11.386 0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12z"/></svg>
                View Source
              </a>
            </div>
            <div class="project-preview">Coming soon</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Project 2 -->
        <div class="project-section reveal">
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-center">
            <div class="md:order-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
                <span class="text-text-dim text-xs tracking-widest" style="font-family: var(--font-mono);">02</span>
                <span class="h-px flex-1 bg-border"></span>
                <span class="text-text-dim text-xs" style="font-family: var(--font-mono);">2026</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-1" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">Trading Arena</h3>
              <p class="text-accent text-sm font-medium mb-5">Real-Time Multiplayer Trading Simulator</p>
              <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">
                A live trading game where players compete to make the most profit. Each round reveals a puzzle — the answer is the contract's settlement price. You trade against other players in real time using a full order book with bids, asks, and position limits.
              </p>
              <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Built the matching engine from scratch — handles price-time priority, partial fills, and live PnL tracking. Players join a room, trade on the order book, and see their positions update instantly via WebSockets.
              </p>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
                <span class="skill-tag">JavaScript</span>
                <span class="skill-tag">Node.js</span>
                <span class="skill-tag">WebSockets</span>
                <span class="skill-tag">Astro</span>
                <span class="skill-tag">SQLite</span>
              </div>
              <a href="https://github.com/IshaanKataria/trading-arena" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-secondary">
                <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 0c-6.626 0-12 5.373-12 12 0 5.302 3.438 9.8 8.207 11.387.599.111.793-.261.793-.577v-2.234c-3.338.726-4.033-1.416-4.033-1.416-.546-1.387-1.333-1.756-1.333-1.756-1.089-.745.083-.729.083-.729 1.205.084 1.839 1.237 1.839 1.237 1.07 1.834 2.807 1.304 3.492.997.107-.775.418-1.305.762-1.604-2.665-.305-5.467-1.334-5.467-5.931 0-1.311.469-2.381 1.236-3.221-.124-.303-.535-1.524.117-3.176 0 0 1.008-.322 3.301 1.23.957-.266 1.983-.399 3.003-.404 1.02.005 2.047.138 3.006.404 2.291-1.552 3.297-1.23 3.297-1.23.653 1.653.242 2.874.118 3.176.77.84 1.235 1.911 1.235 3.221 0 4.609-2.807 5.624-5.479 5.921.43.372.823 1.102.823 2.222v3.293c0 .319.192.694.801.576 4.765-1.589 8.199-6.086 8.199-11.386 0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12z"/></svg>
