        <!-- Project 3 -->
        <div class="project-section reveal">
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 items-center">
            <div>
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-5">
                <span class="text-text-dim text-xs tracking-widest" style="font-family: var(--font-mono);">03</span>
                <span class="h-px flex-1 bg-border"></span>
                <span class="text-text-dim text-xs" style="font-family: var(--font-mono);">2026</span>
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-1" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">Deal Tracker</h3>
              <p class="text-accent text-sm font-medium mb-5">Automated Price Monitoring & Alerts</p>
              <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">
                I kept missing sales on things I wanted to buy. So I built a tool that watches product pages for me, tracks price history in a database, and sends an alert the moment something drops below my target price.
              </p>
              <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Runs on a schedule, scrapes multiple retailers, and stores everything in SQLite. Includes a web dashboard showing price trends over time so you can spot patterns before setting alerts.
              </p>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-6">
                <span class="skill-tag">Python</span>
                <span class="skill-tag">BeautifulSoup</span>
                <span class="skill-tag">SQLite</span>
                <span class="skill-tag">Astro</span>
              </div>
              <a href="https://github.com/IshaanKataria/deal-tracker" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-secondary">
                <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M12 0c-6.626 0-12 5.373-12 12 0 5.302 3.438 9.8 8.207 11.387.599.111.793-.261.793-.577v-2.234c-3.338.726-4.033-1.416-4.033-1.416-.546-1.387-1.333-1.756-1.333-1.756-1.089-.745.083-.729.083-.729 1.205.084 1.839 1.237 1.839 1.237 1.07 1.834 2.807 1.304 3.492.997.107-.775.418-1.305.762-1.604-2.665-.305-5.467-1.334-5.467-5.931 0-1.311.469-2.381 1.236-3.221-.124-.303-.535-1.524.117-3.176 0 0 1.008-.322 3.301 1.23.957-.266 1.983-.399 3.003-.404 1.02.005 2.047.138 3.006.404 2.291-1.552 3.297-1.23 3.297-1.23.653 1.653.242 2.874.118 3.176.77.84 1.235 1.911 1.235 3.221 0 4.609-2.807 5.624-5.479 5.921.43.372.823 1.102.823 2.222v3.293c0 .319.192.694.801.576 4.765-1.589 8.199-6.086 8.199-11.386 0-6.627-5.373-12-12-12z"/></svg>
                View Source
              </a>
            </div>
            <div class="project-preview">Coming soon</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ===== ABOUT ===== -->
    <section id="about" class="py-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="mb-12 reveal">
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold" style="font-family: var(--font-display);">About</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-12">
          <div class="md:col-span-2 reveal">
            <p class="text-text-muted text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
              I'm doing a double degree at Monash — Commerce and IT — because I couldn't pick one. Turns out that's a feature, not a bug. I think about problems from both the business and technical side, which means I build things people actually want to use.
            </p>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
              I got into coding through wanting to automate stuff that annoyed me. That turned into building a stock analyser because I didn't want to pay for Bloomberg, and pulling an all-nighter at a hackathon because the problem was too interesting to sleep on.
            </p>
            <p class="text-text-muted text-lg leading-relaxed">
              I'm interested in startups and want to eventually build my own. Right now I'm stacking skills — working through the Google Data Analytics Certificate, shipping side projects, and looking for the right team to join.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="reveal reveal-delay-1">
            <div class="info-card space-y-4">
              <div>
                <p class="info-card-label">Location</p>
                <p class="font-medium">Melbourne, VIC</p>
